
[1]quinine

   QUIN'INE, n. In pharmacy, a substance prepared from yellow bark
   possessing in a concentrated form, the tonic virtues of the bark, and
   capable of forming salts with acids. One of these, the sulphate of
   quinine, is much employed in intermittent fevers and other diseases,
   where powerful tonics are required.
